          "If enforcement appears likely, the developer should take immediate steps to protect their position. This includes: seeking specialist legal advice on the enforcement process and the developer's rights, exploring urgent refinancing options with alternative lenders (see our guide on <a href=\"/guides/refinancing-distressed-development\">refinancing a distressed development</a>), assessing the personal guarantee exposure and taking advice on managing this liability, and considering whether a consensual resolution (such as a voluntary sale or surrender) might achieve a better outcome than contested enforcement.",
